prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the Hot Ink Comic Poster visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these concrete style rules: full-bleed hot mustard-yellow poster field; one oversized coral-red flat cutout subject occupying about two thirds of the composition; pure black thick hand-drawn marker outlines with rounded uneven joins and ink wobble; no depth, no gradient, no realistic shadow; large coral-filled black-outline hand-lettered headline pushed into a corner or across an edge; small black handwritten microcopy blocks arranged as texture; abstract comic arrows, swoops, starbursts, dot trails, exclamation marks, sticker shapes, and underlines around the subject; scruffy xerox or screenprint finish with imperfect edges and low-tech flyer energy. Preserve the style fidelity anchors before anything else, but use the new subject, new setting, new prop, and new text above. Avoid all source content listed above and avoid any watermark, logo, QR code, username, or platform mark.
